<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Goschen</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-25"><hi rend="italic">August 25,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In response to the inquiry the British
                            ambassador made of me yesterday, when handing me a memorandum of Lord
                            Kimberley’s views touching the effect of the recent tariff legislation
                            upon the commercial agreements made with the West Indies under section 3
                            of the McKinley act, I have the honor to say that the sections to which
                            his lordship refers would, upon the new tariff act becoming a law,
                            operate to cancel those agreements.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>